sic pet on Dapper and backup to the range limit of Lava Bolt.  Cast it 4 times (more is resisted or partially resisted) and finish off with a Scars if you need to.  No kiting, no running, no agro on you, and if you do it right, your pet won't die and will be able to heal to full for the next round.  Anyone who has done the AC in OOT should know this tactic and it is one of the best ways to solo mobs with high hps.<br>
<br>
Kaelum Yodi<br>
57 mage<br>
Fortis (Tunare) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uloathexx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loathexx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(7/14/02 1:57:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Too funny....</span><hr size=1> EEK.  In my opinion, KEI makes about any camp insanely effective, heh.  Heck, I wouldn't even waste my KEI on Dapper.  I'd be out there at the raptors, with KEI...or Scarlet Desert, or somewhere else where I'm not spending more time waiting for a repop, than I am killing.   <p>[IMG]http://www.scienceofwar.net/forums/attachment.php?s=&postid=3431[/IMG]</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usinghaovercast.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Singha Overcast</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#333333>(7/14/02 5:41:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Guards will aggro</span><hr size=1> <br>
Killed Dapper many times with an air pet on Wednesday July 10th 2002 and never got aggro from the guards.<br>
<br>
Went back Friday and when Dapper death-marched back towards the guards they aggro'ed on me. Tried it again on saturday, same thing.<br>
<br>
It seems that if you are pulling Dapper to the hill, when he gets low on HP he walks back to the guards. Once he gets to the big tree right there the guards aggro.<br>
<br>
I switched to earth pet and Dapper never made it back close enough to cause the guards to aggro me.<br>
<br>
I was also talking to a druid who stopped by and he said he was pulling with snare and getting guard aggro. He said that had never happened to him before this weekend. I used malise to pull and no guards ever added that way.<br>
<br>
So it looks like they changed things a bit and added in some risk to the Dapper camp.<br>
<br>
Oh, at 56 I got half a blue per hour here and a bad case of a numb mind from boredom. I think I'll go look for something a bit more lively.<br>
<br>
