It seems that if you are pulling Dapper to the hill, when he gets low on HP he walks back to the guards. Once he gets to the big tree right there the guards aggro.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
when you are on the hill, which is also the north wall, just go and wait <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  on the path</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Pull Dapper with burn. He comes to you, far from guards. When he crosses the path, send pet.<br>
When he's dying, he flies, but flies South west i think, I mean he <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  does not cross path again</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> then guards will never aggro you.<br>
I've been doing that for some weeks now, never got any aggro.<br>
<br>
If he runs to you, run away, but never never cross the path you'll be too close to guards.<br>
